, secret services, data brokers, developers of new technologies, etc., as well as the growing internet of things, big data and non-transparent algorithms speed up the loss of control. Information contexts that used to be separated from each other - intimate, private, public, institutional information - are gradually merging. This is where Thilo Hagendorff starts: He introduces innovative strategies of the use of media that anticipate the loss of control or even fully count on it - and that do not count on vulnerable norms of privacy or unreliable data protection technologies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aBig Data. 4aDatenschutz. 4aDigitale Medien. 4aInformationssicherheit. 4aInternet. 4aMedien. 4aMediennutzung. 4aMediensoziologie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aPrivatsphäre. 4aRecht. 4aTechnik. 4aTechniksoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aBig Data.  aData Protection.  aDigital Media.  aInformation Security.  aInternet.  aLaw.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia Use.  aMedia.  aSociology of Media.  aSociology of Technology.  aTechnology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2017z9783110548242oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839437773zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839437773423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839437773/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGG